                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tyler</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Tyler reports that the American legation and the British minister presented
                    a joint note to the prime minister insisting upon the immediate dispatch of a
                    fully equipped expedition for the capture of the murderers of Labaree.)<note
                        n="a" xml:id="d609fna">Printed on <ref target="#pg_667">page
                        667</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
